  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean, bounded envelope)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is a negative-control (clean) specimen: the ContextOfUse declares a fully structured OperatingEnvelope with concrete flow-rate and rotational-speed bounds and a structured ApplicabilityConstraint scoping the in-domain geometry and fluid properties. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achievedLevel >= requiredLevel. Decision: Accepted.",
