    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 credibility factors assessed with achievedLevel >= requiredLevel. The ContextOfUse declares a fully structured OperatingEnvelope (flow rate 1–7 L/min, speed 2000–3500 RPM, geometry tolerances ±0.15 mm) and a structured ApplicabilityConstraint scoping the FDA benchmark geometry and Newtonian blood analog. Validation evidence covers all 5 operating points densely within the declared envelope. Monte Carlo UQ (N=5000) confirms that the 95th-percentile NIH prediction (0.0083 g/100 L) remains below the clinical threshold (0.01 g/100 L) across the full envelope. GCI < 2.5% confirms discretization adequacy. Independent peer review found zero critical use errors. Model form uncertainty (7.6% NIH spread across three turbulence model variants) is within the accepted threshold. The bounded applicability constraint and operating envelope provide explicit traceability between the validation domain and the intended COU. No credibility gaps remain; the package is accepted for regulatory submission.",
